<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Blind2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Blind,</orth> vb. to deprive of sight, to dazzle: <cit><quote>his eyes began to wink, being --ed with a greater light,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 375" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 375</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>--ing tears,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 16</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>such a sight will b. a father's eye,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 2.4.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. II, 4, 53</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 76</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.76" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 76</bibl> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.228" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 228</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.245" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 245</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.10" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 2.4.167" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. II, 4, 167</bibl>. <emph>a blinded god</emph> == a blindfolded god, <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.201" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. IV, 4, 201</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>